Press any key to continue.
 Explanation To save the highest value in the list, create a local variable called max. To begin the comparison, initialize max with the first element. Then go through the supplied array starting at element two and going all the way to element zero, comparing each element to the maximum. Replace the value of max with the current element if the current element exceeds max. Return and display the value of the greatest array element that was put in max at the end. Using Library Function Example: 
